Claims CLAIMS:  What is claimed is: 1. A method comprising: determining that a user equipment (UE) can support operation on a given radio band combination comprising a first radio band operating with a first radio access technology (RAT) and a second radio band operating with a second RAT; using a performance capability of the UE to obtain at least a second configuration for the second radio band operating with the second RAT; and configuring the UE with the interworking configuration, the interworking configuration comprising a first configuration to operate on the first band with the first RAT and a second configuration to operate on the second band with the second RAT. 2. The method according to claim 1 , wherein the first RAT is evolved universal mobile telecommunications service terrestrial radio access (E-UTRA) radio access technology and the second RAT is third generation partnership project (3 GPP) new radio (NR) or 5 th generation (5G) radio access technology. 3. The method according to claim 2, wherein: the method is performed by a master radio access node operating with the first RAT, the master radio access node provides the first configuration to a secondary access node operating with the second RAT; and the master radio access node obtains the interworking configuration from the secondary access node. 4. The method according to any of claims 1-3, wherein: determining that the UE can support operation on the given radio band combination comprises receiving from the UE a message identifying the given radio band combination and an indicator of the performance capability of the UE, where the indicator indicates the performance capability of the UE on at least the second RAT. 5. The method according to claim 4, wherein the received message includes two indicators of the performance capability of the UE, one of which indicates the performance capability of the UE on the second RAT and the other of which indicates the performance capability of the UE on the first RAT. 6. The method according to any o f claims 1 -5 , wherein using the performance capability of the UE to obtain at least the second configuration comprises: using the performance capability of the UE to determine an expected performance metric for operation on the second RAT; and sending to a secondary radio access node operating with the second RAT a request for the interworking configuration, the request identifying the expected performance metric. 7. The method according to claim 6, wherein the request sent to the secondary radio access node further indicates the first configuration. 8. The method according to any of claims 6-7, wherein the interworking configuration is received from the secondary radio access node along with at least an estimated performance metric for operation on at least the second RAT. 9. The method according to any of claims 1-8, further comprising, after configuring the UE with the interworking configuration, at least one of: receiving from the UE an indication of measured performance on the second RAT; and sending to a secondary radio access node that provided the interworking configuration a request for at least one indication of measured performance on the second RAT. 10. A computer readable memory storing computer program instructions that, when executed by one or more processors, cause a host device to perform actions comprising: determining that a user equipment (UE) can support operation on a given radio band combination comprising a first radio band operating with a first radio access technology (RAT) and a second radio band operating with a second RAT; 

 using a performance capability of the UE to obtain at least a second configuration for the second radio band operating with the second RAT; and configuring the UE with the interworking configuration, the interworking configuration comprising a first configuration to operate on the first band with the first RAT and a second configuration to operate on the second band with the second RAT. 11. The computer readable memory according to claim 10, wherein: determining that the UE can support operation on the given radio band combination comprises receiving from the UE a message identifying the given radio band combination and an indicator of the performance capability of the UE, where the indicator indicates the performance capability of the UE on at least the second RAT. 12. The computer readable memory according to any of claims 10-11, wherein using the performance capability of the UE to obtain at least the second configuration comprises: using the performance capability of the UE to determine an expected performance metric for operation on the second RAT; and sending to a secondary radio access node operating with the second RAT a request for the interworking configuration, the request identifying the expected performance metric. 13. An apparatus comprising: at least one computer readable memory storing computer program instructions, and at least one processor; wherein the computer readable memory with the computer program instructions is configured, with the at least one processor, to cause the apparatus to perform actions comprising: determining that a user equipment (UE) can support operation on a given radio band combination comprising a first radio band operating with a first radio access technology (RAT) and a second radio band operating with a second RAT; using a performance capability of the UE to obtain at least a second configuration for the second radio band operating with the second RAT; and 

 configuring the UE with the interworking configuration, the interworking configuration comprising a first configuration to operate on the first band with the first RAT and a second configuration to operate on the second band with the second RAT. 14. The apparatus according to claim 13, wherein: the first RAT is evolved universal mobile telecommunications service terrestrial radio access (E-UTRA) radio access technology; the second RAT is third generation partnership project (3 GPP) new radio (NR) or 5 th generation (5G) radio access technology; the apparatus comprises a master radio access node operating with the first RAT, the master radio access node provides the first configuration to a secondary access node operating with the second RAT; and the master radio access node obtains the interworking configuration from the secondary access node. 15. The apparatus according to any of claims 13-14, wherein: determining that the UE can support operation on the given radio band combination comprises receiving from the UE a message identifying the given radio band combination and an indicator of the performance capability of the UE, where the indicator indicates the performance capability of the UE on at least the second RAT. 16. The apparatus according to claim 15, wherein the received message includes two indicators of the performance capability of the UE, one of which indicates the performance capability of the UE on the second RAT and the other of which indicates the performance capability of the UE on the first RAT. 17. The apparatus according to any of claims 13-16, wherein using the performance capability of the UE to obtain at least the second configuration comprises: using the performance capability of the UE to determine an expected performance metric for operation on the second RAT; and sending to a secondary radio access node operating with the second RAT a request for the interworking configuration, the request identifying the expected performance metric. 18.